132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 498
H.P. 327 House of Representatives, February 11, 2025
Resolve, to Improve Standards for Animal Rescue Entities
Received by the Clerk of the House on February 6, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed
pursuant to Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative PERKINS of Dover-Foxcroft. (BY REQUEST)
Cosponsored by Senator CYRWAY of Kennebec and
Representatives: BABIN of Fort Fairfield, MCINTYRE of Lowell, MINGO of Calais,
NUTTING of Oakland, WHITE of Guilford.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Sec. 1. Department to adopt rules regarding animal rescue entities.
2 Resolved: That the Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry shall adopt
3 rules that set standards for animal rescue entities, including but not limited to dog rescue
4 operations, that specify staff-to-animal ratios and that govern animals that are returned
5 multiple times and resold or placed in multiple homes. Rules adopted pursuant to this
6 section are routine technical rules as described in the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 5,
7 chapter 375, subchapter 2-A.
8 SUMMARY
99 This resolve requires the Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry to
1100 adopt rules that set standards for animal rescue entities, including but not limited to dog
1111 rescue operations, that specify staff-to-animal ratios and that govern animals that are
1122 returned multiple times and resold or placed in multiple homes.
